        <a name="whatsNew"></a>
        <h3>What's new</h3>
        <p>Esri Maps for Salesforce version 1.2 was released in June 2015. This version includes the following improvements:</p>
        <ul>
			<li><a href="http://doc.arcgis.com/en/maps-for-salesforce/design-maps/map-with-url-parameters.htm">Open map with URL Parameters</a></li>
			<li>Improve load performance</li>
			<li>Enhanced security for map objects that honors settings defined by the sharing rules</li>
			<li>Bug Fixes</li>
        </ul>


        <a name="previousVersions"></a>
        <h3>Previous version</h3>
		<p>Esri Maps for Salesforce version 1.1 was released in March 2015. This version includes:</p>
        <ul>
			<li>Geocoding improvements</li>
			<li>Ability to change the view for layers on-the-fly</li>
			<li>Filter selected records on the records pane</li>
		</ul>
		
		<a name="systemRequirements"></a>
        <h3>System requirements</h3>

        <ul>
		 <li>Esri Maps for Salesforce requires an account that is part of an ArcGIS Online organization and access to Salesforce.</li>
		 <li>Esri Maps for Salesforce supports the following browsers: Internet Explorer 9, Internet Explorer 10*, Chrome, Firefox, and Safari. *Internet Explorer 10 compatibility is limited to the desktop browser and does not extend to the touch-based version.</li>
		</ul>

